Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
specifyInstPad(25.10)                                    specifyInstPad(25.10)

Name
       specifyInstPad - Specifies a value (number of sites) for padding for an
       instance

Syntax
       specifyInstPad

       <instName>

       {<padding>  |  [[-right  <padding>]  [-left <padding>] [-top <padding>]
       [-bottom <padding>]]}

       Specifies a value (number  of  sites)  for  padding  for  an  instance.
       Padding  expands  the  area of an instance, so that the software leaves
       extra space around the instance during global placement (place_design),
       which helps reduce congestion in both the horizontal and  vertical  di-
       rections.   In  detail  placement,  user  should  specify  setPlaceMode
       -place_detail_honor_inst_pad to true to honor  left,  right,  top,  and
       bottom instance padding.

       Adding instance padding reduces horizontal and vertical congestion, but
       also decreases utilization.

       Note: To remove instance padding, use the deleteInstPad command.

       You  can use the reportInstPad to report the padding for a specific in-
       stance, or all instance padding in the design.

Parameters
       -bottom <padding>
              Specifies the amount of padding at the bottom, in terms of  num-
              ber of rows.

       <instName>
              Specifies  the  instance  to pad. You can use wildcards (*) when
              you specify the instance.

       -left <padding>
              Specifies the amount of padding on the left side,  in  terms  of
              number of sites occupied by the instance.

       <padding>
              Specifies  the  amount  of padding to add, in terms of number of
              sites occupied by the instance (sites are  defined  in  the  LEF
              file).

              For  example,  if an instance occupies eight sites, specifying 8
              expands the area horizontally of the instance  by  100  percent,
              and  specifying 12 expands the area horizontally of the instance
              by 150 percent.

              The number you specify must be a whole number that is  equal  to
              or greater than zero.

       -right <padding>
              Specifies  the  amount of padding on the right side, in terms of
              number of sites occupied by the instance.

       -top <padding>
              Specifies the amount of padding at the top, in terms  of  number
              of rows.

Examples
              * The  following command adds padding of 2 sites around instance
                named U27316:

       specifyInstPad U27316 2

              * The following command adds padding of  3  sites  for  all  in-
                stances with prefix U2:

       specifyInstPad U2* 3

